This paper discusses attacks and defenses in machine learning systems, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on the effectiveness of attacks against supervised machine learning systems. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing defenses, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of transferability in the proposed FAIL model could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as transferability is a common concept in these fields. Finally, the paper proposes a targeted poisoning attack, which could fall under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
